						               													<description>Crosshairs is a combinatorial game with a WW1 aerial combat theme. Players each have a squadron of planes and move all of their planes each turn. Movement consists of either &amp;#10;a) a straight pass flight (no altitude change)&amp;#10;b) a climb (increasing the height of the piece by adding an additional ring) or &amp;#10;c) a dive (losing height to make a sequence of moves by removing one ring per descent height). &amp;#10;Pieces are captured when they are in the line of fire of two or more enemy planes. Clouds block line of fire and provide strategic cover during play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a player is reduced to having only one plane, he's shot from the sky (i.e., is eliminated from the game). A player wins when he reduces the only remaining opponent to only one plane. Games are brutal, fast, and fun.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The base game includes components for a 2-player game. If you wish to add more players you'll need the expansion (one per additional player).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;COMPONENTS (NESTORGAMES edition)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Base game (2 players): Board (2 pads), 16 foam clouds, 40 altitude rings (laser cut 8mm 'ice' acrylic), 2 small plastic boxes, 5 red biplanes, 5 green biplanes, carrying case.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Expansion (per extra player): 5 biplanes (orange or yellow), 20 altitude counters, carrying case. Please indicate colour if you purchase one set only. You can see the biplanes in the pictures below.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
